title: PMQs live: Jeremy Corbyn set to challenge David Cameron on tax credits, China and 'steel dumping'
text: Jeremy Corbyn has plenty of ammunition as he takes on David Cameron at Prime Minister's Questions for the third time, with tax credit cuts, threats from China's cheap imports on the British steel industry and the country's poor human rights record all topics that are likely to be raised. Here are the latest updates: Tory MP pleads with Osborne to soften impact of tax credit cuts Corbyn's adviser describes Miliband's cabinet as 's****' Cameron and Xi to seal Â£30 billion deal MPs to launch 'urgent' inquiry into impact of tax credit cuts Tory MP caught laughing during tax credit debate What Jeremy Corbyn actually said when he met Xi Jinping
